<p>Itchy scalp hair loss is a common problem and the treatment you require depends on the relationship between the two problems. You will need to discover whether you are dealing with hair loss as a result of itchy scalp or whether your hair loss is causing your scalp to itch. It is therefore vital you quickly get it diagnosed as to which problem you are dealing with.</p>
<p>Hair Loss as a result of Itchy Scalp</p>
<p>With this scenario your hair loss is from a medical condition, is usually temporary and may be caused by one of the following conditions:</p>
<p>Psoriasis &#8211; This condition can result in temporary baldness and can result in severe itching, often identified by white patches on red skin.</p>
<p>Scalp Ringworm &#8211; This can be a contagious fungal infection. The skin can become red with itchy rash like patches and requires some tough treatment.</p>
<p>Allergic Reaction &#8211; Many shampoos contain harsh chemicals that can damage your hair follicles and cause an allergic reaction resulting in an itchy scalp and possible hair loss.</p>
<p>Before undergoing any type of remedial treatment always seek a Doctors opinion on what condition you are dealing with. This will give you the best chance to sort out the problem quickly.</p>
<p>Itchy Scalp As A Result of Hair Loss</p>
<p>Your Itchy scalp could be a side effect of losing hair as old hair follicles die. If this is the case you could look into hair loss rejuvenation products or natural healing ointments. There are many different types of products to choose from ranging from natural remedies to more potent treatments.</p>
<p>One thing is for sure. Itchy Scalp and hair loss is a distressing time. The quicker you get your problem diagnosed by a Doctor the quicker you can begin the appropriate treatment.</p>
